</span></h1><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-15_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-16_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-17_"><i class="sc-dChVQp hgzReS pf-18_ pfa pfa-book-open-reader" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Dr Richard Dune</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-19_"><i class="sc-dChVQp hgzReS pf-20_ pfa pfa-book-open-reader" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>14-06-2023</h3></div></div></div><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beat_the_Heat_Top_Tips_for_a_Safe_and_Enjoyable_Summer_Workout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686674865" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beat_the_Heat_Top_Tips_for_a_Safe_and_Enjoyable_Summer_Workout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686674865 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beat_the_Heat_Top_Tips_for_a_Safe_and_Enjoyable_Summer_Workout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1686674865 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Beat_the_Heat_Top_Tips_for_a_Safe_and_Enjoyable_Summer_Workout_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686674865 320w" width="1787" height="1091" alt="Beat the Heat: Top Tips for a Safe and Enjoyable Summer Workout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Beat the Heat: Top Tips for a Safe and Enjoyable Summer Workout - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-21_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-af97" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dBFCZX khzvmY pf-22_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gvPcJq dRaLso"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-24_"><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-25_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-27_">The advent of summer, with its sun-kissed skies and inviting warm weather, makes the outdoors an attractive place for fitness enthusiasts. There's an undeniable allure to working out amid nature, taking in the beautiful scenery, and soaking up a healthy dose of vitamin D. But as the mercury rises, exercising outdoors requires more caution. High temperatures can stress your body more, leading to serious heat-related illnesses if you're not careful.
<br><br>As we prepare for the scorching summer months, let's dive into safely maintaining our outdoor exercise routines. Here are some crucial considerations and tips for a safe and enjoyable summer workout regimen.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-28_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-30_">Check the weather forecast
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Check_the_weather_forecast_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675360" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Check_the_weather_forecast_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675360 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Check_the_weather_forecast_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686675360 320w" width="1766" height="1179" alt="Check the weather forecast - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Check the weather forecast - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-31_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-34_">Before setting foot outside for your workout, you must know the day's weather forecast. High temperatures and increased humidity can escalate your workout's intensity as your body has to work harder to cool itself down.
<br><br>On such days, consider reducing the intensity of your workout or opting for indoor exercise. Extreme caution is warranted when the thermometer exceeds 26 degrees Celsius, mainly if you're not acclimated to exercising in such conditions or have underlying health issues.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-35_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-37_">Hydration - Your body's cooling system
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Hydration_-_Your_body_s_cooling_system_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675667" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Hydration_-_Your_body_s_cooling_system_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675667 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Hydration_-_Your_body_s_cooling_system_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686675667 320w" width="1356" height="904" alt="Hydration - Your body's cooling system - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Hydration - Your body's cooling system - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-38_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-39_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-41_">In hot weather, you will sweat more than usual, thus increasing your risk of dehydration. Make it a point to consume water before, during, and after your workout.
<br><br>Consider sports drinks for extended workout sessions, as these can help replenish vital electrolytes lost through sweating. Remember, thirst is a delayed response, indicating you are already dehydrated. So, don't wait until you're thirsty to start sipping water.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-42_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-44_">Dress for heat success
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dress_for_heat_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675816" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dress_for_heat_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675816 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dress_for_heat_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686675816 320w" width="1908" height="1273" alt="Dress for heat success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Dress for heat success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-45_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-46_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-48_">The clothing you choose plays a crucial role in how your body responds to heat. Opt for light-coloured, lightweight, and breathable clothing to help keep your body cool. Hats and sunglasses can provide additional protection for your face and eyes from the scorching sun.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-51_">Timing is everything
</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Timing_is_everything_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675922" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Timing_is_everything_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686675922 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Timing_is_everything_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686675922 320w" width="1570" height="1047" alt="Timing is everything - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Timing is everything - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-52_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-53_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-55_">Try to schedule your workouts in the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/dr-richard-dune/the-5-am-club-purposeful-routines-for-busy-executives" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(84, 152, 228);">early mornings</span></a> or late evenings to avoid the peak heat hours of the day. Exercising during these cooler times can help you avoid unnecessary strain on your body due to excessive heat and ensure a more comfortable workout experience.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-56_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-58_">Sunscreen - Your invisible workout partner
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Sunscreen_-_Your_invisible_workout_partner_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676066" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Sunscreen_-_Your_invisible_workout_partner_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676066 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Sunscreen_-_Your_invisible_workout_partner_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686676066 320w" width="1336" height="891" alt="Sunscreen - Your invisible workout partner - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Sunscreen - Your invisible workout partner - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-59_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-60_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-62_">Sunscreen isn't just for the beach; it should also be a critical part of your outdoor workout gear. A broad-spectrum, water-resistant sunscreen with an SPF of 30 or higher can protect your skin from harmful UV rays. Apply it about 20 minutes before heading outdoors, and remember to reapply every two hours, especially during long workouts, to ensure continuous protection.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-63_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-65_">Listen to your body's wisdom

</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Listen_to_your_body_s_wisdom_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676192" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Listen_to_your_body_s_wisdom_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676192 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Listen_to_your_body_s_wisdom_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686676192 320w" width="1382" height="778" alt="Listen to your body's wisdom - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Listen to your body's wisdom - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-66_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-67_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-69_">Your body is incredibly intuitive and will provide signals if it's struggling with the heat. If you want to sustain <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/blogs/health-wellbeing/the-importance-of-health-and-well-being-for-health-and-social-care-workers" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(84, 152, 228);">better mental health and well-being</span></a>, it is crucial to pay attention to your body and watch out for symptoms like dizziness, nausea, headaches, or confusion. These can be indicators of heat-related illnesses, and if they occur, you should stop exercising, seek a cool place, and rehydrate.

</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-70_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-72_">Heat acclimatisation
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Heat_acclimatisation_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676366" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Heat_acclimatisation_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676366 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Heat_acclimatisation_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686676366 320w" width="1590" height="1061" alt="Heat acclimatisation - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Heat acclimatisation - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-73_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-74_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-76_">Your body needs time to adjust to exercising in the heat. During the initial days of hot weather, consider reducing the duration or intensity of your workouts. Gradually increase them as your body becomes acclimated to the higher temperatures.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-77_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-79_">Dive into the water
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dive_into_the_water_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676495" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dive_into_the_water_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676495 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Dive_into_the_water_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686676495 320w" width="1341" height="924" alt="Dive into the water - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Dive into the water - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-80_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-81_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-83_">Consider changing up your workout routine with water-based activities. Whether swimming laps in the local pool or simply taking a dip in the ocean, water activities are a great way to stay active while keeping cool. Plus, <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/benefits-of-swimming" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(84, 152, 228);">swimming provides</span></a> a fantastic full-body, low-impact, yet highly effective workout.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-84_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-86_">Keep an eye on air quality
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Keep_an_eye_on_air_quality_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676602" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Keep_an_eye_on_air_quality_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1686676602 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Keep_an_eye_on_air_quality_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1686676602 320w" width="1680" height="735" alt="Keep an eye on air quality - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Keep an eye on air quality - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gtJxSR jkHSry pf-87_"/><p class="sc-eONOlN cfGtgs pf-88_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-90_">Hot weather can sometimes lead to poor air quality, making breathing challenging during intense workouts, particularly for individuals with respiratory issues. Always check the local air quality index before you plan to exercise outdoors.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-fUklNj thmnJ pf-91_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cHMHbD bwTmDt pf-93_">Take it indoors

