</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-112_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-113_">Check the weather forecast before exercising outdoors.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-115_">Hydrate properly before, during, and after your workout.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-117_">Wear appropriate, breathable clothing.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-119_">Exercise during the cooler parts of the day.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-121_">Apply and reapply sunscreen.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-123_">Pay attention to your body's signals.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-125_">Acclimatise your body gradually to the heat.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-127_">Consider water-based exercises.
